                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/2885</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-15T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 17, 6.10
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1650. Legation’s 1494, August 22. In answer to an inquiry made at French Foreign
                    Office through the American Embassy Paris am informed with reference to parcels
                    mailed at the fourth-class rate and addressed to American prisoners that the
                    French Line boats transporting these parcels are limited to 1,000 each. Prior to
                    final <pb facs="0094" n="10" xml:id="pg_10"/> decision on this subject Foreign
                    Office wishes to be informed whether United States Government could endeavor to
                    ship by other means the number of parcels in excess of quantity named.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
